Pietermaritzburg born and bred star, Thuso Mbedu, is soaring in Hollywood. The star scooped the best female performance in a scripted series for ‘The underground railroad’ at this year’s Independent Spirit Awards. Mbedu topped the trending twitter charts this morning, with tweeps congratulating her on her win. The underground railroad is Mbedu’s first international debut. The series is based on the novel "The underground railroad' by Colson Whitehead. Mbedu is set to make her film debut this year opposite Hollywood star Viola Davis in ‘The woman king’. 